Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
extract_package(25.10)                                  extract_package(25.10)

Name
       extract_package

Syntax
       extract_package

       [-help] <<domain>>

       [-output <<directoryname>>]

       -pkg_bga_name <<bga_circuitname>>

       -pkg_die_name <<die_circuitname>>

       [-reference_net <<netname>>]

       [-spd_file <filename>]

       -workspace <<workspace_name>>

       Specifies to start package model extraction.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs the command usage and a brief description about the com-
              mand parameters.

       <domain>
              Specifies the rail analysis domain name.

       -output <<directoryname>>
              By  default, the package model will be created in the workspace.
              However, if you specify an output directory, then a copy of  the
              result will be made in the new directory.

       -pkg_bga_name <<bga_circuitname>>
              Defines  the  ball  grid array (BGA) circuit name in the package
              model. It is the PCB component in the package model, which even-
              tually connects to the PCB model.

       -pkg_die_name <<die_circuitname>>
              Defines the die circuit name in the package model.  When  speci-
              fied,  the  software automatically creates a mapping between the
              die name in the package extraction tool and the die name in  the
              software.

       -reference_net <<netname>>
              Specifies  the  ground net that is selected as reference net for
              pin-based model generation. This is the ground net that is being
              referred to by the power nets.

       -spd_file <filename>
              Specifies an existing Sigrity .spd file for package  extraction.
              This  parameter allows you to specify a .spd file instead of the
              workspace name (package model database) of the  package  extrac-
              tion tool (XtractIM).

       -workspace <<workspace_name>>
              Specifies  the  workspace  name  (package model database) of the
              package extraction tool (XtractIM). The file name  extension  is
              .ximx.

Example
              * The following example specifies the package models details and
                starts extraction:

                extract_package ALL \

                  -workspace ../rak_xim_pkg_model/C1_Voltus_4L.ximx \

                  -pkg_bga_name FPBGA144 \

                  -pkg_die_name CD1 \

                  -output rak_xim_pkg_model_voltus_cpf \

                  -reference_net VSS

